        "url": "https://jobs.github.com/positions/100027a4-8b5a-40bb-8f5f-4db6da447472",
        "created_at": "Tue Jul 23 07:44:02 UTC 2019",
        "company": "LINE Fukuoka Corporation",
        "company_url": "https://linefukuoka.co.jp/en/career/",
        "location": "Fukuoka",
        "title": "Software Engineer in Test (SET) - Working in Japan",
        "description": "<h2><strong>Job Description</strong></h2>\n<p>You will be responsible for the planning, proposing, developing and the operation of automation tests that are suitable for various products provided by LINE. Starting from the building of test automation environment to the development and operation of testing platforms, you will be in charge of a wide range of automated tasks.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Creation and operation of UI tests for iOS/Android applications (unit test, E2E test, etc.)</li>\n<li>Building and proposing test environments that match the architecture of various products</li>\n<li>Development and operation of new testing platforms (in accordance with the test automation protocols of our services)</li>\n<li>Building the environment for test automation</li>\n<li>Designing, implementing and executing automated testing using different frameworks</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>【Main Technologies Utilized】</strong></p>\n<p>Java, JavaScript, Swift, Kotlin, Selenium, Appium, XCUITest, Espresso\nJenkins, CircleCI, Drone, Postman, GitHub, JIRA, Confluence, etc.</p>\n<h2><strong>Requirement</strong></h2>\n<p><strong>【Required Skills】</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>3+ years of experience in developing iOS/Android applications or web applications</li>\n<li>Good command of Japanese (JLPT N3 or above)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>*Whilst there are many English speakers at LINE successful applicants may be asked to attend a Japanese training course for at least 3 ~ 12 months after joining. The training is paid for by us, and is an excellent chance to pick up new language skills. We encourage employees to reach JLPT Level 2 within a few years of joining.</p>\n<p><strong>【Preferred Skills】</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Knowledge about software tests and basic knowledge about computer science (algorithms, data structures, databases, networks, etc.)</li>\n<li>Experience in creating and proposing unit tests as well as integration tests that match the architecture and nature of the service</li>\n<li>Work experience using test frameworks, such as Appium/Selenium</li>\n<li>Experience in test automation</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>【Who We’re Looking For】</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Strongly motivated candidates that are highly interested in the IT industry</li>\n<li>Candidates who can think for themselves and who can take initiatives</li>\n<li>Candidates who are willing to make improvements in testing methods</li>\n<li>Candidates who can maintain excellent communication with related parties while running different projects</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Working Hours:</strong></h2>\n<p>Discretionary and flexible according to ability and speed of work; if projects are completed on time there is no need to stay in the office for extended periods of time.</p>\n<h2><strong>Salary:</strong></h2>\n<p>Minimum salary starting from 6 million Japanese yen per annum (salary based on experience and ability).</p>\n<p>*Other details to be discussed during the interview process.</p>\n",
        "how_to_apply": "<p>Please apply via the link below:</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://js01.jposting.net/linefukuoka/u/engineer/entry.phtml?job=220&amp;_ga=2.11836275.63935030.1563778054-295587063.1541670446\">https://js01.jposting.net/linefukuoka/u/engineer/entry.phtml?job=220&amp;_ga=2.11836275.63935030.1563778054-295587063.1541670446</a></p>\n",
