        "location": "New York, NY",
        "title": "Full Stack Developer",
        "description": "<h2><strong>Luckie exists to relentlessly evolve the dynamics of marketing.</strong></h2>\n<p>We are a fiercely independent 66-year-old company that fuses the science of data, insightful strategy and the art of communication to deliver wildly creative marketing that drives radical impact for our clients.</p>\n<h2><strong>Job Description</strong></h2>\n<p>Full Stack Developer will work with development and project teams to deliver usable, functional, websites that meet both design and development specifications.</p>\n<p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p>\n<p>Key Responsibilities</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Write HTML, CSS, JavaScript, PHP, SQL (and use related libraries) to build custom solutions</li>\n<li>Interpret Photoshop documents or other design files to develop webpages that satisfy the creative intent</li>\n<li>Create and Interpret data models/ ER diagrams</li>\n<li>Develop user interface or layouts that are extendable and reusable</li>\n<li>Develop functional modules that are extendable and reusable</li>\n<li>Regularly update status to team and development leads</li>\n<li>Articulate roadblocks and impediments as they occur</li>\n<li>Submit clean and efficient code regularly for review and integration into larger project</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Bonus Points</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Experience with Laravel, Vue, React, and WordPress is a plus</li>\n<li>Architect end to end solutions that are scalable</li>\n<li>Experience writing automated builds</li>\n<li>Ability to support occasionally on nights/weekends</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Required Skills &amp; Traits</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Bachelor’s degree or equivalent experience</li>\n<li>3+ years of digital development</li>\n<li>Responsive, mobile-first web design</li>\n<li>Object Oriented JavaScript</li>\n<li>Bootstrap CSS and JS Experience</li>\n<li>PHP and MySQL Experience</li>\n<li>Continuous Integration experience using Git, Jenkins, etc.</li>\n<li>Engagement and interest in development and project as whole</li>\n<li>Flexibility and ability to adapt in a fast-paced work environment</li>\n<li>Ability to architect technical approaches and adapt per feedback</li>\n<li>Work well in team and unafraid of pair programming</li>\n<li>Eye for visual design and pixel-perfect development as well as ability to interpret and execute on functional requirements</li>\n<li>Familiarity with various developer tools for cross-browser compatibility</li>\n<li>Strong communication skills</li>\n<li>Attention to detail</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Interested?</strong></h2>\n<p>Please apply via <a href=\"https://luckieandcompany.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/full_stack_developer_duluth_ga/252151/V819/solliciteren\">this link</a>.</p>\n<h2><strong>Additional Information</strong></h2>\n<p>PARTIAL CLIENT LIST</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Little Debbie</li>\n<li>Regions Bank</li>\n<li>FedEx</li>\n<li>Williamsburg, Virginia, Tourism</li>\n<li>Panama City Beach Tourism</li>\n<li>Piedmont Healthcare</li>\n<li>GlaxoSmithKline</li>\n<li>Alabama Power</li>\n</ul>\n",
