        "company": "RockCreek",
        "company_url": "https://www.therockcreekgroup.com/",
        "location": "Washington, DC",
        "title": "VP of Engineering",
        "description": "<p>RockCreek is a leading global investment management firm that applies data-driven technology and innovation to sustainable investing. Our portfolio managers invest in emerging markets and alternatives, and our asset allocation teams invest in multi-asset class and outsourced CIO portfolios and customized solutions. RockCreek’s client base is made up of sophisticated institutional investors, including endowments, foundations, pension plans, and sovereign funds. The firm is highly focused on the integration of environmental, social, and governance (ESG) factors and sustainable impact across portfolios to generate long-term returns. RockCreek is a collaborative environment that values openness, transparency, partnership, and knowledge sharing. Diversity, debate and a relentless drive to excel are foundations of our team culture.</p>\n<p>Technology is a key, and growing, part of our service offerings. We are committed to best-of-breed applications, automation, and solutions for managing funds and portfolios across our broad range of investment offerings. In addition to launching a dedicated advanced analytics team, we are currently consolidating our data assets into a large data lake on Amazon Web Services and providing a variety of API and programmatic access patterns.</p>\n<h2><strong>Job Description</strong></h2>\n<p>RockCreek is looking for a VP of Engineering to oversee technical business strategy, provide technical leadership, and build engineering teams with a strong vision and a clear mandate. In addition to having technical knowledge of core engineering fields, you understand how all the pieces fit together into integrated systems and how those systems impact performance.</p>\n<p>The VP of Engineering will bring deep technical skills within a specific domain and excellent communication skills, a focused and empathic approach to leadership, and a bold and action-biased attitude to hard engineering problems:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Set the strategic direction of the engineering team, clearly establishing goals and objectives</li>\n<li>Source, recruit, screen, hire, grow, and retain talent</li>\n<li>Establish a culture of high productivity, collaboration and big impact, and empower each team member to bring their vision to life</li>\n<li>Understand RockCreek’s business and work with team members throughout the company to develop our technology approach</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Qualifications</strong></h2>\n<p>A growth mindset and a bias toward action. You thrive in a fast-paced, entrepreneurial firm and can adapt to changing priorities of a dynamic organization.</p>\n<p>Hands-on development experience with JavaScript, or Ruby on Rails, or Node.js, or React.js</p>\n<p>Familiarity with R, Python, D3.js and Data Science/Visualization tools are a plus</p>\n<p>Practical industry experience working on AI, NLP, machine learning, or statistical analysis projects are a plus</p>\n<p>Prior experience in recruiting, interviewing, and hiring cross-functional technical teams coupled with strong management and people development skills. You’ll need to delegate intelligently, deliver frequent and honest feedback, and deliver results</p>\n<p>Ability to lead end-to-end development and release successful software solutions</p>\n<p>Knowledge of AWS reference architectures, particularly in the context of:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>API Gateway</li>\n<li>Lambda functions and triggers from other AWS managed services\nAppreciation of UI/UX, with understanding of Responsive &amp; Adaptive Design principles</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Disciplined approach to testing &amp; quality assurance</p>\n<p>Experience implementing core business strategies with technology by creating processes that scale, advancing architecture, and developing roadmaps</p>\n<p>Experience managing vendors, budgets and delivery schedules</p>\n<p>BS or MS degree in Computer Science or equivalent</p>\n<h2><strong>Additional Information</strong></h2>\n<h2><strong>Benefits:</strong></h2>\n<p>Consistent with our belief that our team members are our most valuable asset, RockCreek offers a competitive benefits package.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Medical, dental, and vision insurance, dependents eligible</li>\n<li>401(k) retirement plan with company match</li>\n<li>Paid time off, sick leave and company holidays</li>\n<li>Wellness programs including an onsite gym and meditation program</li>\n<li>Healthy snacks and beverages</li>\n</ul>\n<h2><strong>Interested?</strong></h2>\n<p>Please apply via <a href=\"https://therockcreekgroup.redirect.your-jobresponse.com/vp_of_engineering_washington/252131/V819/apply\">this link</a>.</p>\n",
